cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems): The paper focuses on miniaturizing JS applications to run on IoT constrained devices, which are typically embedded systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a multiobjective optimization approach to optimize the performance of JS applications on IoT devices, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper deals with porting a programming language (JavaScript) to run on constrained devices, which falls under the scope of programming languages. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a software optimization approach to improve the performance of JS applications on IoT devices, which is a software engineering problem. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper briefly mentions the hardware constraints of IoT devices, which can be seen as a hardware architecture problem.
